# Steam Friend Relationship Map - Developer Rules (.cursorrules)

This file defines the core project description, architecture, file structure, roadmap references, and security development rules. All AI assistants and developers contributing to this project must strictly adhere to these rules.

---

## 1. Project Description & Core Architecture

### 1.1 Project Overview
This project is a locally run **Steam Friend Relationship Map Analysis & Visualization Tool**. Users input a public Steam profile URL. The tool treats this user as the Root node and uses a Breadth-First Search (BFS) algorithm to crawl public friend relationships downward by 1-4 levels. The data is saved in a local Neo4j graph database and visualized as an interactive graph in a local Web GUI.

### 1.2 Core Architecture
- **Backend**: FastAPI provides asynchronous RESTful APIs, managing BFS crawl states and graph queries.
- **Graph Database**: Neo4j Desktop (running locally, connected via Bolt protocol).
- **Frontend**: Single-Page Application (SPA) built with HTML5, Vanilla CSS, and ES6 JavaScript. Cytoscape.js renders the graph. Multi-language support is provided via `i18n.json` (Chinese/English).
- **Environment & Dependency Management**: Python 3.12+ managed by `uv` (executed using `uv sync` and `uv run`).

---

## 2. Project Directory & File Structure

Developers and AI models must maintain the following file organization and respect each file's dedicated responsibility:

```text
Steam-Friend-Relationship-Map/
├── pyproject.toml                     # Project metadata & dependency declarations (managed by uv)
├── uv.lock                            # Lock file containing locked dependencies
├── README.md                          # User documentation & startup instructions
├── roadmap.md                         # Project roadmap and feature plans (Reference: Section 3)
├── SECURITY.md                        # Security & vulnerability reporting policy
├── PRIVACY.md                         # Privacy policy & data protection guidelines
├── .cursorrules                       # AI assistant instructions & project guidelines (this file)
├── src/
│   └── steam_friend_relationship_map/ # Main package source directory
│       ├── __init__.py                # Package initializer
│       ├── __main__.py                # Command-line entry point mapping to `steam-friend-map` executable
│       ├── app.py                     # FastAPI server initialization, routers, endpoints, and middleware
│       ├── crawler.py                 # BFS crawl runner, manages async task loops, delay, and filter pipeline
│       ├── logs.py                    # Custom AppLogBuffer & handler mapping to redact secrets in logs
│       ├── models.py                  # Pydantic schemas, models, and validator rules for API requests/responses
│       ├── neo4j_repo.py              # Neo4j repository layer containing database connectivity & Cypher queries
│       ├── secrets.py                 # Keyring wrapper to securely store/fetch secrets from system credential stores
│       ├── settings.py                # System settings loader based on Pydantic-settings
│       ├── steam.py                   # Steam API wrapper handling profile resolving, summaries, and friend lists
│       └── static/                    # Frontend SPA resources
│           ├── index.html             # Dashboard UI structure (sidebar controls, main canvas, detail inspector)
│           ├── app.js                 # Frontend application logic, API queries, & Cytoscape.js rendering
│           ├── styles.css             # Glassmorphism visual theme, custom layout, and responsive styles
│           ├── i18n.json              # Localized text resource mapping (en / zh-CN)
│           └── vendor/                # Third-party frontend assets (cytoscape.min.js, lucide.min.js)
└── tests/                             # Automated test suite
    ├── test_app.py                    # FastAPI route & payload schema tests using TestClient & mock repository
    ├── test_crawler.py                # Crawl BFS logic, node limits, and candidate filtering rules (via Fakes)
    ├── test_steam.py                  # Steam client query resolving & private profile handling tests
    ├── test_i18n.py                   # Translating-key symmetry checks between en & zh-CN in i18n.json
    └── test_neo4j_queries.py          # Static syntax checkers verifying compatibility with Neo4j 5.0+ COUNT clauses
```

